WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:11.730 position:69%
Graco Children's Products is voluntarily
recalling about 1.5 million Graco's Passage,

00:00:11.730 --> 00:00:15.640 position:70%
Alano and Spree Strollers and Travel Systems.

00:00:15.640 --> 00:00:21.450 position:66%
The hinges on the stroller's canopy pose a
fingertip amputation and laceration hazard

00:00:21.450 --> 00:00:26.230
to the child when the consumer
is opening or closing the canopy.

00:00:26.230 --> 00:00:30.270
Graco has received seven reports
of children placing their fingers

00:00:30.270 --> 00:00:35.490 position:69%
in the stroller's canopy hinge mechanism
while the canopy was being opened or closed,

00:00:35.490 --> 00:00:41.260 position:61%
resulting in five fingertip amputations
and two fingertip lacerations.

00:00:41.260 --> 00:00:46.800 position:64%
This recall involves Graco Passage, Alano
and Spree strollers and travel systems

00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:53.620 position:63%
with certain model numbers and specific
hinge mechanisms included in this chart.

00:00:53.620 --> 00:00:59.480 position:67%
Graco manufactured two different styles of
hinge mechanisms for these stroller models.

00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:03.150 position:66%
Only strollers or travel systems with this
[jpg of affected hinge only here] plastic,

00:01:03.150 --> 00:01:09.970 position:75%
jointed hinge mechanism that has indented canopy
positioning notches are included in this recall.

00:01:09.970 --> 00:01:16.420 position:63%
The recalled strollers were manufactured
between October 2004 and February 2008.

00:01:16.420 --> 00:01:21.060 position:61%
The model number and manufacture date
are located on the lower inside portion

00:01:21.060 --> 00:01:24.920 position:72%
of the rear frame, just above the rear wheels.

00:01:24.920 --> 00:01:33.500 position:72%
They were sold at these and other retailers
nationwide from October 2004 and December 2009

00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:42.280 position:70%
for between $80 and $90 for the strollers and
between $150 and $200 for the travel systems.

00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:46.860 position:63%
Consumers should immediately stop using
the recalled strollers and contact Graco

00:01:46.860 --> 00:01:49.530 position:72%
to receive a free protective cover repair kit.

00:01:49.530 --> 00:01:52.820
Consumers can install this
repair kit themselves.

00:01:52.820 --> 00:01:56.280
You put these covers over
each side canopy hinge.

00:01:56.280 --> 00:02:02.820
For more information contact
Graco at (800) 345-4109,

00:02:02.820 --> 00:02:07.880
or visit the firm's Web site
at www.gracobaby.com.

